<br>
She sweapt the papers off her desk an a sudden outburst of rage.  Thousands of platinum went into the procurement of these ancient maps of Neriak.  Old tunnels and catacombs and escape passages carefully mapped, all of them useless.<br>
<br>
Countless amounts of resources of House K'Thalion where spent in the last few days.  People, platinum, magic, all of it gained the House nothing.  Shaede growled in frustration.  She had to find Nospiratus.  She knows Mythral has him.  She is powerless to stop any of this.<br>
<br>
&quot;NO!&quot;, Shaede called out.  Immediately two attendents were opening the door.  Her two personal custos always at ready since her last trip to the Grange. Would it be her last trip, she wondered to herself?<br>
<br>
The Harvest was torn.  Faeolin acting in ways not normal for the tempermental warrior.  Vresk, acting undiscplined and confused.  Even the Reaper showed an outburst of emotion, an unchecked response to Hatred, that betreyed his normal control of his emotions.<br>
<br>
She dismissed the two custos without an explination, the two left without argument, leaving her alone to her thoughts.  She sat back into her chair, aching with the need of Xareth, the need to feel him next to her confirming her existance.  She leaned back, a dark wicked smile playing across her face.  For the first time in weeks she felt the dark play of Innoruuk's hatred play across her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mythral, you have made a fatal mistake my friend.&quot;  Shaede started to call forth a spell, and at the moment of completion, threw a malachite in the air.  She watched it swirl, then dissapear as it coallesced into her elemental. Opening a small chest of summoned items she placed them on her elemental, knowing full well that these items would make it near invulnerable to magic.  &quot;Oh yes, you brought the accusations against me to the Harvest, hoping to break me completely.  The Mad One is gone,&quot; she wrapped the blanket around her own shoulders, feeling the magic emcompass her &quot;but the Mad Ones wisdom is bound to his house.&quot;  Her eyes flashed darkly, &quot;And you...You should never have backed me into a corner.&quot;<br>
<br>
Reaching to her desk she grasped a book and some maps and placed them into a dimensional pocket.  Calling to her custos she bid them to enter.  &quot;Talis'shar, K'rillian come with me.  Carry these.&quot; She pointed to a stack of the dimensional bags.  As she walked out she left explicet instructions with her house.  Immediately runners went to find Xareth, in Nektulous and Daiunus.<br>
<br>
Quickly with her two custos and her pet behind her Matron Shaede K'Thalion, Dread Lord to the Harvest and Elementalist of Innoruuk stood before the gates of House S'Therik. Stepping toward the gates she spoke to one of the skeletal guardians, knowing the Reaper would be given the message.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell Khasirath I have arrived, the time is upon us.&quot;<br>
<br>
